# CODEOWNERS — review routing for URDF Studio  (SKELETON / NOT YET ACTIVE)
#
# Every rule below is intentionally commented out. This file is a scaffold: it
# records WHICH paths warrant mandatory review, but routes nothing until a
# maintainer (1) replaces the @OWNER-* placeholders with real GitHub handles or
# teams and (2) uncomments the rules they want enforced.
#
# Why commented: an active CODEOWNERS that references an unknown user/team makes
# GitHub flag every matching PR, and — under branch protection that requires
# code-owner review — can BLOCK merges. Keeping it inert avoids disrupting
# in-flight work; activate deliberately, path group by path group.
#
# Syntax:  <path-glob>  <owner> [<owner> ...]   (the LAST matching rule wins)
# Docs:    https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners

# --- Default ----------------------------------------------------------------
# *                                                   @OWNER-CORE

# --- Architecture guardrails (size / dependency gates, CI) ------------------
# These encode the project's red lines; changes here loosen or tighten what the
# whole repo is allowed to do, so they deserve a careful second pair of eyes.
# /scripts/tools/google_style_audit.mjs               @OWNER-CORE
# /scripts/tools/google_style_baseline.json           @OWNER-CORE
# /scripts/tools/dependency_boundaries.mjs            @OWNER-CORE
# /scripts/tools/dependency_boundaries_baseline.json  @OWNER-CORE
# /eslint.config.mjs                                  @OWNER-CORE
# /.github/workflows/                                 @OWNER-CORE
# /CLAUDE.md                                          @OWNER-CORE
# /docs/architecture.md                               @OWNER-CORE

# --- Largest / highest-churn feature ----------------------------------------
# urdf-viewer is ~20% of src/; until the Phase 2 USD split lands it is the
# single riskiest place to change.
# /src/features/urdf-viewer/                          @OWNER-VIEWER

# --- Parsers (consider splitting to per-format owners) ----------------------
# /src/core/parsers/urdf/                             @OWNER-PARSERS
# /src/core/parsers/mjcf/                             @OWNER-PARSERS
# /src/core/parsers/sdf/                              @OWNER-PARSERS
# /src/core/parsers/usd/                              @OWNER-PARSERS
# /src/core/parsers/xacro/                            @OWNER-PARSERS

# --- State layer (cross-cutting; a bad store change reaches everything) ------
# /src/store/                                         @OWNER-CORE

# --- Hand-written C-ABI WASM + its generated artifacts ----------------------
# Single-translation-unit emscripten sources and their generated glue/binary;
# see docs/wasm-build.md. Editing the .cpp or regenerating public/wasm needs the
# toolchain owner.
# /src/core/loaders/wasm/                             @OWNER-WASM
# /public/wasm/                                       @OWNER-WASM

